<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,763,1222]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis box="[136,204,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Herbs</emphasis>
, ca. 
<quantity box="[255,298,763,790]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
tall. 
<emphasis box="[352,458,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Branches</emphasis>
green, cylindrical, costate. 
<emphasis box="[763,841,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Leaves</emphasis>
opposite, sessile, concolorous, blades ca. 4.5 × 
<quantity box="[1369,1447,763,790]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" unit="cm" value="2.6">2.6 cm</quantity>
, narrow-elliptic, subcoriaceous, glabrous, attenuated at base, acute at apex, entire at margin. 
<emphasis box="[1171,1321,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Inflorescence</emphasis>
in terminal cymes, 11-flowered, peduncle ca. 
<quantity box="[522,582,835,862]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[593,685,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Flowers</emphasis>
homostylous, 5-merous, pedicel ca. 
<quantity box="[1100,1181,835,862]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" unit="cm" value="3.5">3.5 cm</quantity>
; calyx ca. 1.2 × 
<quantity box="[1367,1447,835,862]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" unit="cm" value="0.5">0.5 cm</quantity>
, green, not winged, not keeled, glabrous, tubular; corolla reddish, hypocrateriform, tube ca. 
<quantity box="[1183,1243,871,898]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" unit="cm" value="4.0">4 cm</quantity>
, lobes ca. 
<quantity box="[1366,1447,871,898]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" unit="cm" value="0.5">0.5 cm</quantity>
, lanceolate, at apex acuminate; stamens 
<quantity box="[580,688,907,934]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" unit="cm" value="2.6" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.2">2.2–3 cm</quantity>
, heterodynamous, adnate, conation 
<quantity box="[1091,1158,907,934]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
, anthers dorsifixed; ovary ca. 8 × 
<quantity box="[219,286,943,970]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, style ca. 
<quantity box="[396,475,943,970]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" unit="cm" value="2.4">2.4 cm</quantity>
, stigma bilobed. 
<emphasis box="[666,724,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Fruit</emphasis>
septifragal capsule.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="71" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,763,1222]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,486,979,1005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Habitat and distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gilg" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="Chamisso &amp; Schlechtendal" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[521,842,979,1005]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Calolisianthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pedunculatus">
<emphasis box="[521,842,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Calolisianthus pedunculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation collectionCode="ER" location="Cerrado" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Santa Catarina">
is found in regions of “campo rupestre” and 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E75B53FFC69E1881C223973D0B4DAC:8E91BC9EFFC69E18841B22F63CDB4A84" box="[1361,1451,979,1005]" name="Cerrado" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" stateProvince="Santa Catarina">Cerrado</location>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[198,362,1015,1041]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
to the 
<collectingRegion box="[439,504,1015,1041]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Bahia</collectingRegion>
portion of the 
<collectionCode box="[672,711,1016,1042]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15275" name="Universität Erlangen-Nürnberg" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" type="Herbarium">ER</collectionCode>
, with confirmed occurrences for the states of 
<collectingRegion isEnumeration="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Bahia, Goiás, Minas Gerais, São Paulo, Paraná and Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
(Calió 2009, 
<bibRefCitation author="Calio, M. F. A. &amp; Guimaraes, E. F. &amp; Saavedra, M. M. &amp; Melo, A." box="[799,987,1051,1078]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" refId="ref12841" refString="Calio, M. F. A., Guimaraes, E. F., Saavedra, M. M. &amp; Melo, A. (2015) Gentianaceae. Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 117 (accessed 7 January 2019)" type="url" year="2015">
Calió 
<emphasis box="[866,923,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1010,1098,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="11.[136,229,1736,1758]" captionTargetBox="[341,1247,190,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[340,1247,190,1712]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 3. Species of Gentianaceae from the Parque Municipal de Mucugê - Projeto Sempre Viva (PMM), Bahia, Brazil: Calolisianthus pedunculatus (A), Chelonanthus purpurascens (B), Curtia verticillaris (C), Curtia tenuifolia (D), Prepusa montana (E), Schultesia bahiensis (F), Schultesia crenuliflora (G), Schultesia pachyphylla (H). Scale bars:A: 2 cm; B: 1 cm; C: 0,5 cm; D: 0,5 cm; E: 2 cm; F–H: 1 cm. Photo A, B, E, F, G and H by Maria Luiza Silveira de Carvalho; C and D by Vinicius Dittrich and Gustavo Shimizu, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424491/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
, Appendix 1)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="71" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,763,1222]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1087,1113]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Comments</emphasis>
:—This species can be readily recognized by the reddish corolla and the fistulous branches (
<bibRefCitation author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." pageId="10" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis box="[136,192,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). Can be collected with flowers and fruits all year round (Calió 2009, 
<bibRefCitation author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[1043,1267,1123,1149]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis box="[1143,1199,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
